review_blob: My favourite mainstream ale! One cannot ignore that Carlsberg HAS heightened their ambitions, and efforts like this one will definitely help improve the general beer climate as some beer beginners may be more open to this than to a snobbish micro thing.
Pretty uncharacteristic for an ale, but the element of honey goes straight through. I would say that its heather honey. Goes very well with many types of food.
Surprisingly good (especially considering the price) for a mass produced beer to be. The touch of elderflower is absolutely welcome. I think Tuborg is on right track.
Interesting mix of aromas. I especially like the elderflowerness about it. Beautiful color.

Not bitter, and no taste but water and lemon. I will never buy this beer myself again, but still I welcome it on the market as I prefer the youth to drink this beer(?) instead of alco-sodas. This brew was never meant to satify beer-lovers.
A massive dark colour, almost black. The taste is characterized by bitterness and malt, that later on, gives room for more coffee- and chocolate-like flavors. Uhm.

Quiet golden pilsner-color, aroma reminds me of wet corn. Not good! The weak taste of malt disappears after a very short while, and only a very irritating, almost rancing, taste stays. I wont recommend this brew, even though its pretty cheap.

Beuatiful yellow-brown foggy look. Aroma dominated by apple perhaps and some citrus-like tones. Nice malted (rye) flavor. Winter Rye was a very pleasent experience. It is also positive that its price is decenting.
Lovely fruity aroma. The flavor is wide, featuring nice malty undertones, a strong hoppy bitternes, and perhaps a hint of apple. Very aromatic. Not at all as weak and strengthless as Heineken.

Hazy amber colour. Malty aroma. Good and fruity flavor..
Perfect in company with a good dinner.
Carlsberg is burning again (semper ardens).

Heineken is just not interesting at all.
Of course it goes down (as we say in Denmark), but thats just not enough.
(too) Easy to drink. The pure hoppy taste is ok.

It was a pleasure to, at last, taste the Budvar. Which is a part of the new danish trend, of buying imported specialities (at a triple price).
Good, but not really that good. Nice yellow color, and nice hoppy after-taste..

Thin/light pale color, sharp aroma with lemon tones. Light bitter taste, that dosnt stay very long. Not anything special, but, I think its better that Carlsberg brewed this celebration-beer, than if they just have been passive.

Ooh, I really love this Hvidtl. It origins from the danish king Christian the 4s brewhouse in Copenhagen, but is now brewed by Tuborg.
Sweet and not very carbonated, with lovely hints of fruit, and the wonderful balanced flavor of chocolate and caramel. The best in its class.
Very flowery flavor, that I havnt tasted before. And never will again. Too strange to me, but it was a nice experience anyway.

I wonder where this name comes from. It does not taste like a bock. But when you've realized that, it tastes very nice. 
Super Pils would be better name. ;-)
UPDATED: JUN 22, 2005

Vestfyen has been lucky with this one. Fine taste that dosent stay for hours.
I know that labels are not rated, but it seems funny that it has barcodes all over.
Very interesting beer, with a well balanced taste (and content) of yeast.  Fruity and a little bit spicy taste.
Beautiful golden color, very nice hoppy aroma, but unfortunately very thin.

Not special at all. This beer has the (for its type) normal malt smell and taste though its here not very strong. I do also think that the add of corn does a too heavy impact on the smell.
Perhaps would this beer do better in a bread ;-)
UPDATED: SEP 27, 2004

Starts thinking how life in Denmark would be, if we still didnt have any beers but theese Hvidtls. (Not good).
Thor Hvidtl is very thin, and is a pretty sweet one in its category. Has a smell of corn, which is a shame.
This was too thin. Has an attractive aroma, but the taste is disappointing.
This Pilsener, brewed by a local german brewery, has a very bitter taste. The rest of its tastes was very normal for a beer of that kind.
UPDATED: AUG 14, 2004
